Package com.composum.platform.feature.nodesstarter

Class LaunchFromEmbeddedFAR

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.composum.platform.feature.nodesstarter.LaunchFromEmbeddedFAR
  • public class LaunchFromEmbeddedFAR
extends Object
    Uses the sling feature launcher to start from the embedded feature archive. This takes the same arguments as the Sling feature launcher and some additional ones: see OPTION_PIDFILE, START_COMMAND. If there is no feature given or there is a parameter -f default, we use the feature embedded into the JAR at DEFAULT_SLING_FEATURE_MODEL_FILE_PATH. If there is no URL given, or there is a parameter -u default, we pass as repository URL the embedded directory /lib (see DEFAULT_REPOSITORY_PATH_MARKER), which is meant to contain the felix framework in a maven-repository like way.

    There is also the additional argument form to stop the process: see StopFromPid.

    See Also:
    StopFromPid
